  "title": "Example of a grayscale release using argo rollouts",
  "type": "lab",
  "description": "Grayscale releases, also known as canary releases, are used to smoothly transition between old and new versions of a product. This involves having both versions in the production environment, and gradually increasing the number of users on the new version. This method reduces the impact of the release and allows for observation of the new version's effects. Argo rollouts is a Kubernetes Controller that includes powerful Deployment capabilities such as grayscale releases, blue-green deployments, and progressive delivery. Installation involves creating a namespace and running commands to install the server-side and client-side components. The grayscale release in Argo rollouts involves two processes: Replica Shifting and Traffic Shifting, which can be tested separately.",
